The paper deals with geometric graphs, which are a fundamental topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The focus is on sparse graphs, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of data structures (cs.DS). The concept of dilation is a measure of the distortion of distances in a graph, which is a topic in both discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm for computing the graph, which falls under the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.SI).
